HEADWORD: Coston lights
<hw>Cos"ton lights</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <def>Signals made by burning
lights of different colors and used by vessels at sea, and in the
life-saving service; -- named after their inventor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

